        Insight | The Sunday Times Sunday, August 9, 2020 | B12 As a nation, we can be empathetic to others, to new ideas, and embrace openness and inclusivit­y Tee Zhuo What does a united Singapore mean to you?
A red and white flag with a crescent moon and stars, perhaps raised each morning to the voices of young people singing, as one, a song of hope and progress.
A shield flanked by a lion and a tiger, embossed in gold on the bright red cover of a small booklet that says: “I am a Singaporea­n.”
A flower in hues of violet and pink, adorning keepsakes for visitors to fondly remember their days in the Garden City. NDP 2020 live coverage across ST’s platforms VIDEO LIVE BLOG LIVE SHOWS ON STRAITSTIM­ES.COM From 8.30am 55 people share why they love Singapore Get live updates, photos and videos throughout the day: Also available on Facebook and YouTube: Singapore residents of different ages, races and nationalit­ies tell us what they love about the country: str.sg/ndp2020blo­g str.sg/stndp str.sg/ndp55 Follow the action at the Padang and various heartland locations islandwide From 9.30am: #STHEARTLAN­DNDP ON INSTAGRAM MICROSITE All you need to know about
